title: HISTORY OF POP AND ROCK MUSIC - part 509
description:
PART  509



            EVA CASSIDY & KATIE MELUA - What A Wonderful World (2007)



     "What a Wonderful World" is a song written by Bob Thiele and George David Weiss. It was first recorded by Louis Armstrong and released as a single in 1967. Thiele and Weiss were both prominent in the music world (Thiele as a producer and Weiss as a composer/performer). Armstrong's recording was inducted in the Grammy Hall of Fame in 1999. The publishing for this song is controlled by Memory Lane Music Group, Carlin Music Corp., and Bug Music, Inc.
Katie Meluaand Eva Cassidy covered this song to raise money for the Red Cross.This version reached #1 in the UK chart in December 2007.
